The VGG16 model is a deep learning model that is widely used for image classification tasks. It was originally developed by researchers at the Visual Geometry Group at Oxford University.The weights in the file are in the TensorFlow format, with the dimensions ordered according to the TensorFlow convention. The file size is 58.89 MB.Using pre-trained weights in deep learning models can be very helpful, especially when you have limited data or computational resources.
